name: Elijah Vue
summary: Human remains discovered in Two Rivers, Wisconsin, have been positively identified as belonging to 3-year-old Elijah Vue, who went missing in February. The remains were found during the ongoing search for the boy, who vanished from Two Rivers on February 16th. DNA testing confirmed the identity of the remains, and the Two Rivers Police Department has shared that the family is devastated by the news. The community in Two Rivers has expressed sadness and condolences following the confirmation of Elijah's death, as they had been closely following the search efforts for the missing boy.
